cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to improve the comprehension of procedural text. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves incorporating commonsense knowledge and large-scale corpora, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of neural structured prediction tasks indicates that it could be relevant to cs.LG (Learning). The paper also mentions the use of images, which could relate to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the use of biasing reading with preferences from large-scale corpora suggests that it could be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
